From 384f18408c32797143059baeb06316a3b0cace42 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: lumaparallax <257510328+lumaparallax@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Tue, 14 Apr 2026 14:46:06 +0900
Subject: [PATCH 15/16] feat(frontend): Implement native Termux APT plugin
 manager

The standard OBS desktop plugin manager relies on fetching JSON manifests
and pre-compiled binaries, which is incompatible with the Termux environment.

This commit introduces a custom, Android-specific plugin manager:
- Added `frontend/plugin-manager-aarch64` utilizing native `apt-cache` and
  `dpkg` commands to manage Debian-packaged plugins.
- Features a rewritten Idian-based UI with persistent disk caching for instant
  load times and synchronous execution to ensure environment stability.
- Updated `feature-plugin-manager.cmake` to compile this module exclusively
  when `OS_ANDROID` is detected.
- Conditionally routed headers in `OBSApp.cpp`, `SourceTreeItem.cpp`, and
  `OBSBasic.cpp` using `__ANDROID__` macros to ensure standard Linux builds
  remain unaffected.
