+++ b/frontend/plugin-manager-aarch64/README.md
@@ -0,0 +1,16 @@
+# OBS Plugin Manager (Aarch64 / Termux)
+
+This directory contains a custom, mobile-optimized Plugin Manager specifically designed for the Android/Termux port of OBS Studio.
+
+## Architecture Differences
+The official desktop OBS plugin manager relies on fetching JSON manifests and managing binaries directly. In a Termux environment, plugins must be compiled natively for `aarch64` and managed via the system package manager (`apt`/`dpkg`) to ensure strict dependency resolution and environment stability.
+
+## Features
+* **Native Package Management:** Hooks directly into `apt-cache`, `apt`, and `dpkg` to search, install, update, and remove plugins natively on Android.
+* **Smart Disk Caching:** Utilizes a persistent local JSON cache (`apt_cache.json`) to provide instant, 0-second UI load times. System polling only occurs on the first boot or when explicitly requested via the Refresh button.
+* **Synchronous Stability:** Package operations execute synchronously to guarantee zero memory leaks, prevent zombie processes, and ensure clean application shutdowns.
+* **Smart Dependencies:** Runs dry-runs (`apt -s`) to warn users of installation sizes and complex dependency chains before execution.
+* **Fallback Metadata:** Gracefully handles missing `Installed-Size` or custom `X-Display-Name` metadata from local DEB packages.
+
+## Build Integration
+This module replaces the standard `plugin-manager` during the CMake build process when the Android target is detected.
